column11:
  We derive explicit expressions for the parameter derivatives
$[\partial^{2}P_{
u}(z)/\partial
u^{2}]_{
u=0}$ and
$[\partial^{3}P_{
u}(z)/\partial
u^{3}]_{
u=0}$, where $P_{
u}(z)$ is the
Legendre function of the first kind. It is found that {displaymath}
 rac{\partial^{2}P_{
u}(z)}{\partial
u^{2}} igg|_{
u=0}
=-2\Li_{2} rac{1-z}{2}, {displaymath} where $\Li_{2}z$ is the dilogarithm
(this formula has been recently arrived at by Schramkowski using
\emph{Mathematica}), and that {displaymath}
 rac{\partial^{3}P_{
u}(z)}{\partial
u^{3}} igg|_{
u=0}
=12\Li_{3} rac{z+1}{2}-6\ln rac{z+1}{2}\Li_{2} rac{z+1}{2}
-\pi^{2}\ln rac{z+1}{2}-12\zeta(3), {displaymath} where $\Li_{3}z$ is the
polylogarithm of order 3 and $\zeta(s)$ is the Riemann zeta function.

